    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Nephi",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 19,
        "summary": "Nephi makes plates of ore and records the history of his people\u2014The God of Israel will come six hundred years from the time Lehi left Jerusalem\u2014Nephi tells of His sufferings and crucifixion\u2014The Jews will be despised and scattered until the latter days, when they will return unto the Lord. About 588\u2013570\u00a0B.C.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that the Lord commanded me, wherefore I did make plates of ore that I might engraven upon them the record of my people. And upon the plates which I made I did engraven the record of my father, and also our journeyings in the wilderness, and the prophecies of my father; and also many of mine own prophecies have I engraven upon them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Plate; Record Keeping.",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scribe.",
                        "start": 179,
                        "end": 187
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 1:17 (16\u201317); 6:1 (1\u20133); Jacob 7:26 (26\u201327).",
                        "start": 205,
                        "end": 211
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I knew not at the time when I made them that I should be commanded of the Lord to make these plates; wherefore, the record of my father, and the genealogy of his fathers, and the more part of all our proceedings in the wilderness are engraven upon those first plates of which I have spoken; wherefore, the things which transpired before I made these plates are, of a truth, more particularly made mention upon the first plates.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 5:30; Jacob 3:14.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:2 (1\u20135); Omni 1:1.",
                        "start": 348,
                        "end": 360
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 44
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And after I had made these plates by way of commandment, I, Nephi, received a commandment that the ministry and the prophecies, the more plain and precious parts of them, should be written upon these plates; and that the things which were written should be kept for the instruction of my people, who should possess the land, and also for other wise purposes, which purposes are known unto the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 10:1; Jacob 1:1 (1\u20134); 3:13 (13\u201314); 4:1 (1\u20134).",
                        "start": 194,
                        "end": 206
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:5 (4\u20135); W\u00a0of\u00a0M 1:7; D&C 3:19 (19\u201320); 10:38 (1\u201351).",
                        "start": 344,
                        "end": 348
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, I, Nephi, did make a record upon the other plates, which gives an account, or which gives a greater account of the wars and contentions and destructions of my people. And this have I done, and commanded my people what they should do after I was gone; and that these plates should be handed down from one generation to another, or from one prophet to another, until further commandments of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:4 (2\u20135); 2\u00a0Ne. 5:33.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And an account of my making these plates shall be given hereafter; and then, behold, I proceed according to that which I have spoken; and this I do that the more sacred things may be kept for the knowledge of my people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 5:30 (28\u201333).",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Preservation of.",
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 187
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless, I do not write anything upon plates save it be that I think it be sacred. And now, if I do err, even did they err of old; not that I would excuse myself because of other men, but because of the weakness which is in me, according to the flesh, I would excuse myself.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "See title page of the Book of Mormon. TG\u00a0Sacred.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 8:17 (13\u201317); Ether 12:23 (23\u201328).",
                        "start": 208,
                        "end": 216
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the things which some men esteem to be of great worth, both to the body and soul, others set at naught and trample under their feet. Yea, even the very God of Israel do men trample under their feet; I say, trample under their feet but I would speak in other words\u2014they set him at naught, and hearken not to the voice of his counsels.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 15:31 (30\u201331); 2\u00a0Ne. 33:2; Jacob 4:14; D&C 3:7 (4\u201313).",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 34:19; D&C 76:35. TG\u00a0Blaspheme; Sacrilege.",
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 184
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience; Prophets, Rejection of.",
                        "start": 296,
                        "end": 307
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And behold he cometh, according to the words of the angel, in six hundred years from the time my father left Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Betrayal of; Jesus Christ, Birth of; Jesus Christ, Prophecies about.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 2:4; 10:4 (4\u201311); 2\u00a0Ne. 25:19.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the world, because of their iniquity, shall judge him to be a thing of naught; wherefore they scourge him, and he suffereth it; and they smite him, and he suffereth it. Yea, they spit upon him, and he suffereth it, because of his loving kindness and his long-suffering towards the children of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 50:6 (5\u20136); Matt. 27:30.",
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 187
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kindness.",
                        "start": 241,
                        "end": 249
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 258,
                        "end": 272
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the God of our fathers, who were led out of Egypt, out of bondage, and also were preserved in the wilderness by him, yea, the God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, yieldeth himself, according to the words of the angel, as a man, into the hands of wicked men, to be lifted up, according to the words of Zenock, and to be crucified, according to the words of Neum, and to be buried in a sepulchre, according to the words of Zenos, which he spake concerning the three days of darkness, which should be a sign given of his death unto those who should inhabit the isles of the sea, more especially given unto those who are of the house of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 10:3; 26:12; Mosiah 7:27; 27:31 (30\u201331); Alma 11:39 (38\u201339); 3\u00a0Ne. 11:14 (14\u201315).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 15:14 (13\u201314); Ex. 3:10 (2\u201310); 6:6; 1\u00a0Ne. 5:15; 17:24 (24, 31, 40); 2\u00a0Ne. 25:20; D&C 136:22.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 32:9; Matt. 22:32; Mosiah 7:19; D&C 136:21. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Jehovah.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 133
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Condescension of.",
                        "start": 182,
                        "end": 190
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Betrayal of.",
                        "start": 265,
                        "end": 271
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 27:14; 28:6.",
                        "start": 283,
                        "end": 292
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "BD\u00a0Lost books. See also Alma 33:15; 34:7; Hel. 8:20 (19\u201320); 3\u00a0Ne. 10:16 (15\u201316).",
                        "start": 320,
                        "end": 326
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 6:9; Mosiah 3:9. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Crucifixion of.",
                        "start": 338,
                        "end": 347
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 27:60; Luke 23:53; 2\u00a0Ne. 25:13.",
                        "start": 403,
                        "end": 412
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 5:1; 6:1; Hel. 15:11.",
                        "start": 440,
                        "end": 445
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:4 (4\u20135); Hel. 14:27 (20, 27); 3\u00a0Ne. 8:19 (3, 19\u201323); 10:9.",
                        "start": 491,
                        "end": 499
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 16:1 (1\u20134).",
                        "start": 643,
                        "end": 658
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p10",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 45
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thus spake the prophet: The Lord God surely shall visit all the house of Israel at that day, some with his voice, because of their righteousness, unto their great joy and salvation, and others with the thunderings and the lightnings of his power, by tempest, by fire, and by smoke, and vapor of darkness, and by the opening of the earth, and by mountains which shall be carried up.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 5:16.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 9:1 (1\u201322).",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 14:21 (20\u201327); 3\u00a0Ne. 8:6 (5\u201323).",
                        "start": 206,
                        "end": 217
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 19:28; Ex. 19:18; Morm. 8:29 (29\u201330); D&C 45:41 (40\u201341).",
                        "start": 279,
                        "end": 284
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:5.",
                        "start": 290,
                        "end": 295
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 23:44 (44\u201345). TG\u00a0Darkness, Physical.",
                        "start": 299,
                        "end": 307
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 16:32; 2\u00a0Ne. 26:5.",
                        "start": 335,
                        "end": 340
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 10:13 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 349,
                        "end": 358
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And all these things must surely come, saith the prophet Zenos. And the rocks of the earth must rend; and because of the groanings of the earth, many of the kings of the isles of the sea shall be wrought upon by the Spirit of God, to exclaim: The God of nature suffers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 14:28 (20\u201328); 3\u00a0Ne. 10:11.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 5:1.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 27:51 (51\u201354).",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:56 (48\u201356).",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And as for those who are at Jerusalem, saith the prophet, they shall be scourged by all people, because they crucify the God of Israel, and turn their hearts aside, rejecting signs and wonders, and the power and glory of the God of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 23:38 (37\u201339); Luke 23:28 (27\u201330).",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And because they turn their hearts aside, saith the prophet, and have despised the Holy One of Israel, they shall wander in the flesh, and perish, and become a hiss and a byword, and be hated among all nations.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 22:6; Mosiah 14:3 (3\u20136).",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 24:9; 3\u00a0Ne. 29:8 (8\u20139). TG\u00a0Israel, Bondage of, in Other Lands.",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 164
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:37; 1\u00a0Kgs. 9:7 (6\u20137); Joel 2:17; 3\u00a0Ne. 16:9 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 177
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 10:6; 25:15. TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 186,
                        "end": 191
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless, when that day cometh, saith the prophet, that they no more turn aside their hearts against the Holy One of Israel, then will he remember the covenants which he made to their fathers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:19; 22:12 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Restoration of.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, then will he remember the isles of the sea; yea, and all the people who are of the house of Israel, will I gather in, saith the Lord, according to the words of the prophet Zenos, from the four quarters of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 22:4; 2\u00a0Ne. 10:21.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 49:22 (20\u201322); 60:4. TG\u00a0Israel, Gathering of.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, and all the earth shall see the salvation of the Lord, saith the prophet; every nation, kindred, tongue and people shall be blessed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 40:5 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 46
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I, Nephi, have written these things unto my people, that perhaps I might persuade them that they would remember the Lord their Redeemer.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 13:29.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, I speak unto all the house of Israel, if it so be that they should obtain these things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Enos 1:16; Morm. 5:12; 7:9 (9\u201310). TG\u00a0Israel, Restoration of.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, I have workings in the spirit, which doth weary me even that all my joints are weak, for those who are at Jerusalem; for had not the Lord been merciful, to show unto me concerning them, even as he had prophets of old, I should have perished also.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 10:8 (8\u201312); 1\u00a0Ne. 1:7; Alma 27:17; Moses 1:10 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he surely did show unto the prophets of old all things concerning them; and also he did show unto many concerning us; wherefore, it must needs be that we know concerning them for they are written upon the plates of brass.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 17:13; Amos 3:7. TG\u00a0Prophets, Mission of.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 10:16 (16\u201317).",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now it came to pass that I, Nephi, did teach my brethren these things; and it came to pass that I did read many things to them, which were engraven upon the plates of brass, that they might know concerning the doings of the Lord in other lands, among people of old.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 13:23; 22:1.",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 172
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I did read many things unto them which were written in the books of Moses; but that I might more fully persuade them to believe in the Lord their Redeemer I did read unto them that which was written by the prophet Isaiah; for I did liken all scriptures unto us, that it might be for our profit and learning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 17:14; 1\u00a0Ne. 5:11; Moses 1:41 (40\u201341).",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 1:1; 1\u00a0Ne. 15:20; 2\u00a0Ne. 25:5 (2\u20136); 3\u00a0Ne. 23:1.",
                        "start": 218,
                        "end": 224
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Value of.",
                        "start": 236,
                        "end": 241
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 4:15.",
                        "start": 291,
                        "end": 297
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore I spake unto them, saying: Hear ye the words of the prophet, ye who are a remnant of the house of Israel, a branch who have been broken off; hear ye the words of the prophet, which were written unto all the house of Israel, and liken them unto yourselves, that ye may have hope as well as your brethren from whom ye have been broken off; for after this manner has the prophet written.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 19:31.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 49:22 (22\u201326); 1\u00a0Ne. 15:12 (12, 16); 2\u00a0Ne. 3:5 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Study of.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 155
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}